{
  "stem": "14810.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And the streets were muddy, it wasn't paved.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "There was about two feet of mud.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "Put them on another pile, and then pick it up, other pile, bring them back.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "And it was just, just to torture us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "In the beginning, I couldn't comprehend that humans can, human race can stoop so low.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "You looked at inmates.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "Everybody-- they were skinny skeletons.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "And there was no friendship, everybody was dog-eat-dog.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "It was literally a jungle-- a jungle.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "It was survival of the fittest.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "That was Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "It was unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "This-- actually they made-- they degraded us, dehumanized and humiliated us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "We became, literally, animals.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "People looked on the street.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "Anything, just to-- any scrap you could find on the-- any-- trash cans, anything.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "All your mind was concentrated on food.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "You know, they gave us in the morning-- all they gave us is a half a pound of bread, and the bread was mixed with sawdust.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "And it was-- most of the time, it was hard as a rock because it was mildew because they kept it in the warehouse for months.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "And all they gave-- and a piece of margarine, which it wasn't real margarine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "It was some kind of substitute.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "And a cup of coffee, chicory coffee.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "It was cold, no sugar.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 79,
      "text": "And that was all they gave you in the morning to eat.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 80,
      "text": "And in afternoon they gave you a little soup.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 81,
      "text": "It was impossible to survive with this kind of food.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 82,
      "text": "The average lifespan was six weeks, from four to six weeks.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 83,
      "text": "Most of them never made it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 84,
      "text": "And then the, the suicide rate was unbelievable there in Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 85,
      "text": "The boys just fell apart.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 86,
      "text": "Like I say, the only way you survived, you had to have an extraordinary strong will to live.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
